&lt;strong&gt;Abstract:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
A spectacular fossil trove on the Arctic island of Spitsbergen shows that marine life made a stunning comeback after Earth‚Äôs greatest extinction. Tens of thousands of fossils reveal fully aquatic reptiles and complex food chains thriving just three million years later. Some predators grew over five meters long, challenging the idea of a slow, step-by-step recovery. The find rewrites the early history of ocean ecosystems.
